Text: Hello, welcome to ALLURE! I'm Ally and I want to teach everyone how to solve a Rubik's Cube.
Today we'll learn the different moves you need to know to solve the white cross.
Would you like to hear more about the white cross and how we will learn the moves?
Level 1
Level: 1

In level 1, we can see that all the color stickers of the white-color edge pieces are paired with their matching color centerpiece, but to acheive the White Cross the white stickers need to pair with the white center piece too
Turn the front face until the white-green edge piece completes the White Cross.
Click solve whenever you are ready
Solve
Watch the cube to see the moves being performed.
Nice job!
Choose another level or repeat this one:
Level 2
Level: 2
In level two, we want the green sticker of the white-green edge to pair with the green centerpiece
Since the white sticker of the edge piece is on the down face, rotate the down face until the green stickers match.
After you have performed these moves, you can use the skills you learned in level 1 to put the white-green edge piece in place.
Click solve whenever you are ready
solve
Watch the cube to see the moves being performed.
You're doing awesome!

Level: 3
For level 3, we want the green sticker of the white-green edge to pair with the green centerpiece
The moves that I'll give you will be determined by whether the white sticker of the edge piece is on the left or right face
To pair the green stickers perform: l
After you have performed these moves, you can use the skills you learned in level 1 to put the white-green edge piece in place.
Click solve whenever you are ready
solve

level 4
Level: 4
To complete level 4 we need both the white and green stickers of the white-green edge piece to be paired with their centerpieces, but only the white stickers are currently paired
Depending on your configuration, the moves to pair the green stickers depend on whether the white-green edge piece is on the left or right face so feel free to try this level multiple times
To pair the green stickers perform the following moves: r	u	'	r	'	u

Hello, welcome to ALLURE! I'm Ally and I want to teach everyone how to solve a Rubik's Cube.
Today we'll learn the different moves you need to know to solve the white cross.
Would you like to hear more about the white cross and how we will learn the moves?
Yes
Let's talk about the white cross!

First, what does the white cross even look like? On the UP face, the white cross will have the white centerpiece with the white edge pieces forming the cross. It is also important that color stickers of the white edge pieces are paired with their matching color centerpieces.
We can see an example of the white cross below.

Today, I'll teach you the moves to solve the white cross by focusing on putting the white-green edge piece in its correct place. By learning these moves for the white-green edge piece, you can apply them to the other white edge pieces and solve the white cross.
Continue
We've broken the moves you need to know into different levels which will gradually increase in complexity.
In each level, I'll guide you through finding the white-green edge piece and how you can move it to put it in place.
To see the move performed on the virtual cube, just type in 'Solve'.

Today, I'll teach you the moves to solve the white cross by focusing on putting the white-green edge piece in its correct place. By learning these moves for the white-green edge piece, you can apply them to the other white edge pieces and solve the white cross.
Continue
We've broken the moves you need to know into different levels which will gradually increase in complexity.
In each level, I'll guide you through finding the white-green edge piece and how you can move it to put it in place.
To see the move performed on the virtual cube, just type in 'Solve'.
